A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Mayor Carlos Greer on his outstanding public service; and
2 for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Mayor Carlos Greer has long been recognized by the citizens of this state for
4 the vital role that he has played in leadership and his deep personal commitment to the
5 welfare of the citizens of Georgia; and
6 WHEREAS, he has diligently and conscientiously devoted innumerable hours of his time,
7 talents, and energy toward the betterment of his community and state, as evidenced
8 dramatically by his superlative service as the first African American mayor of Locust Grove,
9 Georgia; and
10 WHEREAS, a lifelong resident of Locust Grove, Mayor Greer previously served the city for
11 nine years as a councilman, including six years as Mayor Pro Tem, during which time he
12 worked diligently to advance the city's progress and improve the quality of life for its
13 residents; and
