14 WHEREAS, Mayor Greer's significant organizational and leadership talents, remarkable
15 patience and diplomacy, keen sense of vision, and sensitivity to the needs of the citizens of
16 this state have earned him the respect and admiration of his colleagues and associates; and
17 WHEREAS, he is a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation for
18 integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness; and
19 WHEREAS, Mayor Greer has served with honor and distinction, and his vision and
20 unyielding commitment to the citizens of Locust Grove have set the standard for public
21 service; and
22 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
23 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately recognized.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
25 the members of this body recognize and commend Mayor Carlos Greer for his efficient,
26 effective, unselfish, and dedicated public service to Locust Grove, Georgia, as well as extend
27 the most sincere best wishes for continued health and happiness.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
29 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
30 Mayor Carlos Greer.
